title: Lynda - Learning the Packet Delivery Process
description: Join Mark Jacob for an exploration of packet-delivery topics like understanding port numbers, establishing a TCP session, and exploring basic IP routing. He'll help you understand the function of routing, and what a media access control (MAC) address really is. Plus, learn about modifying packet information with network address translation (NAT) and managing traffic using access control lists (ACLs)
